{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2993].
  {panel}

Over a long period of time, Jira users leave the company or change email addresses and dissappear. This means that any issues or notification schemes that refer to them continue trying send them emails and leave the inbox with 100's of "delivery failures".

We would like to be able to disable users' email notifications in this instance.

-Nick

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2990].
  {panel}

If a user reports and issue, and it is determined it is a duplicate, add the option to set a watch for the report of the duplicate issue for the parent issue.  This way duplicate issue reporters can be notified when the parent issue is resolved/closed.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
