  {panel}

Is there a reason why custom fields should be limited to just issues?  This issue created to link to individual requests/use-cases..

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2979].
  {panel}

Recently on a JIRA install, I had the need to record some extra information relating to attachments, namely whether copyright for the attachment had been assigned to the organization hosting the JIRA instance (a checkbox).  If JIRA allowed custom fields on attachments, this would have been easy to do.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2971].
  {panel}

I use Apple's iCal application for my calendaring needs.  It has the ability to subscribe to a published calendar (via HTTP).  This published calendar appears as a separate calendar entity within iCal and is a read-only view of the data.  iCal seems to support both events (including alarms) and tasks (todos; along with due dates) from a subscribed calendar.

I envision JIRA providing a calendar feed that I could subscribe to that would show tasks that I need to attend to (bugs, issues, tasks, etc.) as well as upcoming due dates, like releases.  I think this feed could be fed from the same information that drives the current dashboard view.  I've come to use iCal to see all kinds of information on a single calendar view, and, coupled with iSync, can also carry this calendar on my Palm.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2968].
  {panel}

(from Noel on IRC)

Occasionally one needs to bulk-delete groups, as when clearing a database of all but a few projects.  The group browser has a 'Del' link next to each group, so each must be deleted individually, which can be a PITA.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2947].
  {panel}

I noticed that at this time we are not able to modify our home View.  I think it would be a nice feature to add columns to existing tasks for each of our users.

Owen Fellows added:
Add the ability to say which columns should be displayed in the Assigned to Me and In Progress portlets.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2937].
  {panel}

(From Noel on IRC)

In JIRA Enterprise, it would be nice if one could associate a permission scheme with a Category.  Projects in this category would then inherit the category's permission scheme, except where overridden.  This would allow the permission scheme for many projects to be changed in one place.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2932].
  {panel}

When ANY entity is created using jelly, it should be possible to specify a key so that the entity can be referred to later in the script using the key rather than the internal id.

This feature exists at the moment for project and issue creation, but we need it for permission schemes, i.e. the <CreatePermissionScheme ... > tag needs a key attribute.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2931].
  {panel}

Set "allow unassigned issues" on
In the filter definition chooes Assignee "any user" finds also unassigned issues. 
I would expecte that "any user" means any user but not no user :) my mistake?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-2923].
